{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648083","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648083"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:49:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:49:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18273"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18273"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10987"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81717"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10987","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10987"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18273"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67017"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7437"},{"type":"tags","id":"7441"},{"type":"tags","id":"10221"},{"type":"tags","id":"10227"},{"type":"tags","id":"11443"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25524"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25527"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/81717"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements is true regarding the knee joint?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It is a modified hinge joint","It consists of two separate joint capsules","It only allows flexion and extension","It is primarily a ball-and-socket joint","It does not include the patella"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe knee joint, one of the largest and most complex joints in the body, plays a crucial role in weight-bearing and movement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe knee joint is correctly described as a \u003Cstrong\u003Emodified hinge joint\u003C/strong\u003E. This means it primarily allows flexion and extension, but also permits a small degree of rotation when the knee is flexed. The knee joint consists of two main articulations: the tibiofemoral joint and the patellofemoral joint, both enclosed within a single joint capsule.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt consists of two separate joint capsules\u003C/strong\u003E - The knee joint has a single joint capsule encompassing both the tibiofemoral and patellofemoral joints\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt only allows flexion and extension\u003C/strong\u003E - The knee also allows a small degree of rotation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is primarily a ball-and-socket joint\u003C/strong\u003E - The knee is not a ball-and-socket joint; it is a modified hinge joint\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt does not include the patella\u003C/strong\u003E - The patella is an integral part of the knee joint, forming the patellofemoral articulation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The knee joint is a modified hinge joint, allowing flexion, extension, and a small degree of rotation.","The knee joint consists of two articulations: the tibiofemoral and patellofemoral joints.","The knee joint is enclosed within a single joint capsule."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67017"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18273"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67017","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67017"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-26T20:15:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-26T20:16:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10987"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81717"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"e